STBLKeyStringList.Text: Who needs a fancy new activity table when some imagination and a little cardboard can create something entirely new.
Crafty Little Car Activity Table
Bring your backyard campout to the next level with this semi-comfy fold-up bed with folding legs that keep you off of the cold hard ground.
Underneath the Stars Fold-Up Bed
Roast marshmallows and stay warm with this sturdy and safe firepit. Perfect for your backyard!
Cozy Backyard Firepit
Why buy a dollhouse when you can just make your own? And why build a regular house when you can build a rocket house? The possibilities are endless!
Up, Up into the Stars Dollhouse
Special Don't Wake the Llama Yeti Edition.
Don't Wake the Llama Yeti Edition
This string of lights is really low to the ground. Maybe it's for ambiance? Perhaps they're string lights for ants!
String Lights for Ants

Nothing says 'backyard charm' like a jar full of fireflies. Luckily, these mini string lights from the hardware store only cost a few Simoleons, and no real fireflies were captured to create this cute outdoor lamp.
Jar Full of Fireflies
This lamp is sturdy enough for outdoor use and cute enough to go anywhere with your space-obsessed little one.
Light My Way to the Moon Lamp
Why stay indoors to watch television when you can hang up a blanket and project the TV on it to enjoy every warm summer night.
Backyard TV Projector
Keep the wet grass from ruining your late-night backyard adventures with this waterproof lawn blanket.
Outdoor Lawn Blanket
When your parent won't splurge on a new tent, some blankets and PVC do the job just fine!
Ultimate Fantasy Blanket Fort
A pillow is a must-have for every sleepover. It's always good to bring your own with you, just in case you get a bit homesick.
Bring Your Own Pillow
Pop-up books are loads of fun. This one is left open to the best part of the story.
Pop-Up Storytime
This sweet little gnome has a weakness for marshmallowy goodness on a warm summer's night.
The Sweetest Little Gnome
No backyard sleepover is complete without a smorgasbord of gooey, chocolatey treats!
More Smores
Backyard campouts need lots of surfaces. When you run out, you make do with what you can find!
Makeshift Shelf
This chair comes in a variety of little pals in little critter form. Perfect for your little one.
Little Pals Folding Chair
These chairs were found in the back of an old abandoned shed. They may not be the most comfortable, but they get the job done!
Needs Paint Backyard Chair
TV nights under the stars require a lot of seating. When you run out, an upturned crate and cozy blanket could end up being the best seat in the house.
Makeshift Extra Seating
Cozy backyard campouts are 10 times better with some sweet tunes. Play your favorites on the Kitty Tunes Radio.
Kitty Tunes Radio
The backyard can be a big scary place, even for the bravest little Sim. If you feel a little overwhelmed, Stuffie is here to be a friend.
Bigfoot Stuffie
Lights? A little blanket? Could this swing set get any cozier?
Cozy Little Swing Set
This table was found in the back of an old abandoned shed. It may need a little paint, but it's perfect for a cozy backyard meal.
Needs Paint Dining Table
Need a table in a hurry? This folding table is perfect for all of your on-the-go surface-related needs.
Little Outdoor Folding Table
This gaming table was found in the back of an old abandoned shed. It may need a little paint, but it's perfect for a game of cards or a round of Don't Wake the Llama!
Needs Paint Game Table
Some folks say that backyard camping isn't real camping, but we all start somewhere. Get plenty of make-believe time in with the Little Camping Buddy until you're ready for the real thing.
Little Camping Buddy
Don't Wake the Llama

Backyard Campout
